    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-03-13</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2017-09-29T22:13:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Social Security Child Protection Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends title II (Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance) of the Social Security Act to direct the Social Security Administration (SSA) to issue a new Social Security number to a child under the age of 14&nbsp;if the confidentiality of the child's previous number has, in the course of the SSA's transmission to the child of its&nbsp;documentation,&nbsp;been compromised due to the theft of that documentation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>17</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-04-13</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-04-17T19:14:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Social Security Child Protection Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Social Security Administration&nbsp;(SSA) to issue a new Social Security number to a child under the age of 14&nbsp;if the confidentiality of the child's previous number has, in the course of the SSA's transmission to the child of&nbsp;a Social Security card,&nbsp;been compromised due to the theft of that card.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>36</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-04-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-04-23T18:08:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <br /><b>Social Security Child Protection Act of 2018</b> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill directs the Social Security Administration&nbsp;(SSA) to issue a new Social Security number to a child under the age of 14&nbsp;if the confidentiality of the child's previous number has, in the course of the SSA's transmission to the child of&nbsp;a Social Security card,&nbsp;been compromised due to the theft of that card.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
